items.title: Cubs rout Mets for sweep, 3 up on MIL, STL
items.summary: What's the best way to deal with getting swept at home? The Cubs responded by pulling off a sweep of their own, beating the Mets, 14-6, on Thursday night at Wrigley Field. Anthony Rizzo smacked his 32nd home run and finished a triple shy of the cycle, and Jason Heyward hit a three-run homer to spark the Cubs, who had lost three in a row to the Brewers last weekend.

items.title: The best two-way players in MLB history
items.summary: When Shohei Ohtani comes to the Major Leagues, the temptation to use him as a two-way player will be great, but the history of successful two-way players in MLB history is limited, to say the least.
